      <description>&lt;div id=&#34;outline-container-headline-1&#34; class=&#34;outline-2&#34;&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;headline-1&#34;&gt;
Emacs, Org and Hugo? ox-hugo
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div id=&#34;outline-text-headline-1&#34; class=&#34;outline-text-2&#34;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We could use org-hugo, but hugo has support for rendering org
natively, so it might be easier to just  write directly.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
It needs a header with a few extra information, it can be done in
org-tags (see &lt;a href=&#34;https://blog.hidasy.xyz/posts/20210824185856-treslechescake/&#34;&gt;Tres Leches Cake&lt;/a&gt; for an example), but my template uses
the hugo version.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div id=&#34;outline-container-headline-2&#34; class=&#34;outline-3&#34;&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;headline-2&#34;&gt;
Linking
&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div id=&#34;outline-text-headline-2&#34; class=&#34;outline-text-3&#34;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.google.com&#34;&gt;Linking works&lt;/a&gt;, just add an org like&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div id=&#34;outline-container-headline-3&#34; class=&#34;outline-3&#34;&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;headline-3&#34;&gt;
Images
&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div id=&#34;outline-text-headline-3&#34; class=&#34;outline-text-3&#34;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;images work, but alt-text is weird, captions are better.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
